import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gender'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')

    plt.legend()

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['type'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, shadow=False, legend=True, fontsize=14)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of incident types resulting in death?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    neighborhood_counts = data.groupby('neighborhood').count().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of incidents across different neighborhoods?', wrap=True)
    plt.bar(neighborhood_counts['neighborhood'], neighborhood_counts['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Neighborhood')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
